    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-10-16T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-10-16T19:00:00-05:00" n="218"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d218">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.90/58a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Thailand</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grant</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-10-16T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 16, 1940—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>66. Your 117, October 12, 3 p.m.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Department suggests that you inform the Deputy Minister for Foreign
                        Affairs that you perceive no objection to the inclusion in a proposed public
                        statement by the Thai Government of a reference to the communication to that
                        Government of the statement made by the Secretary of State on July 16,
                            1937,<note n="23" xml:id="d218fn23">
                            <ref target="frus1931-41v01#pg_325">
                                <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, Japan, 1931–1941, vol. <hi
                                    rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 325</ref>.</note> and of a reference
                        to the Secretary of State’s public statements of April 17,<note n="24"
                            xml:id="d218fn24">
                            <ref target="frus1931-41v02#pg_281">
                                <hi rend="italic">Ibid.</hi>, vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, p.
                                281</ref>.</note> May 11,<note n="25" xml:id="d218fn25">
                            <ref target="frus1931-41v02#pg_285">
                                <hi rend="italic">Ibid.</hi>, p. 285</ref>.</note> and September 4,
                            1940<note n="26" xml:id="d218fn26">Department of State <hi rend="italic"
                                >Bulletin</hi>, September 7, 1940, p. 196.</note> in regard to the
                        question of the <hi rend="italic">status quo</hi> in the Pacific area, but
                        that you consider that it would be inappropriate to make reference in such
                        public statement to views which were expressed by you orally and informally
                        to officials of the Thai Government in regard to the matter under
                        reference.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>We have carefully considered the suggestion contained in the third
                        paragraph of your telegram under reference and have concluded that the
                        considerations contra outweigh those pro.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
